usdAaaMIB.name: usdAaaMIB

revisions.description: Added support for additional AAA objects: usdAaaAssignSubscriberLimit, usdAaaAcctSendStopOnAaaDeny, usdAaaAcctSendStopOnAaaReject, usdAaaTunnelIgnoreNasPort, usdAaaTunnelIgnoreNasPortType, usdAaaTunnelAssignmentIdFormat, usdAaaSubscriberPseudoCount, usdAaaSubscriberPseudoPeakCount.
Added interface location-relative subscriber management attributes under usdAaaSubscribers. Increase ranges for usdAaaSessionTimeout and usdAaaAcctInterval.
Added subscriber management attributes under usdAaaSubscribers, capabilities management attributes under usdAaaCapabilities.

Added assignment delimiter attributes: usdAaaAssignDomainDelimiters usdAaaAssignRealmDelimiters usdAaaAssignDomainParseOrder usdAaaTunnelClientName usdAaaTunnelPassword usdAaaTunnelNasPortMethod; also, resized: usdAaaAssignDomainTunnelHostName usdAaaAssignDomainTunnelServerName

Added parameters to the usdAaaAssignDomainTunnelTable: usdAaaAssignDomainTunnelServerName usdAaaAssignDomainTunnelClientAddress Added usdAaaDupAddrCheck, usdAaaIdleTimeout and usdAaaSessionTimeout parameters.

Added ATM traffic shaping parameters to usdAaaAssignDomainTable. Added usdAaaAssignDomainTunnelTable. Added 'dhcp' as an option for usdAaaAddrAddrPoolDefault; use of the value 'none' has been discontinued. Added statistics to track the performance of AAA.
Initial version of this MIB module.

usdAaaMIB.contactinfo: Unisphere Networks, Inc. Postal: 10 Technology Park Drive Westford, MA 01886 USA Tel: +1 978 589 5800 Email: mib@UnisphereNetworks.com
usdAaaMIB.description: The Authentication, Authorization and Accounting (AAA) MIB for the Unisphere Networks enterprise.

UsdAaaDomainName.name: UsdAaaDomainName
UsdAaaDomainName.description: The name of an internet domain. Represents textual information taken from the NVT ASCII character set.
UsdAaaDomainName.reference: RFC 854: NVT ASCII character set. See SNMPv2-TC.DisplayString DESCRIPTION for a summary.

UsdAaaAuthenticationMethods.name: UsdAaaAuthenticationMethods
UsdAaaAuthenticationMethods.description: The set of configurable authentication choices. The maximum enumerated type will never be greater than 255.

UsdAaaAccountingMethods.name: UsdAaaAccountingMethods
UsdAaaAccountingMethods.description: The set of configurable accounting choices.

UsdAddressAssignType.name: UsdAddressAssignType
UsdAddressAssignType.description: The set of possible AAA address assignment sources.

UsdSubscriberState.name: UsdSubscriberState
UsdSubscriberState.description: The set of possible AAA subscriber states, expressed as a bit map: init Initial state (transient) pending Auth/Acct or Addr Request is pending established Subscriber is authenticated deleting Deletion of subscriber is pending tunneling Subscriber is being tunneled tunnelAcct Tunnel accounting is enabled terminated Subscriber has been terminated More than one state bit can be active simultaneously. If no bits are set, the subscriber is in a transient initial state.

UsdSubscriberClientType.name: UsdSubscriberClientType
UsdSubscriberClientType.description: The set of possible AAA subscriber client types: ppp PPP client login Command line interface or SSH ip IP-based application config Locally configured client identity tunnel Tunnel e.g. L2TP other Unspecified client type

UsdSubscriberLocationType.name: UsdSubscriberLocationType
UsdSubscriberLocationType.description: Describes the platform-dependent interpretation of a UsdSubscriberLocationValue object: unknown Unspecified/unknown slotPort Two octets in length; first octet is 'slot', second octet is 'port'

UsdSubscriberLocationValue.name: UsdSubscriberLocationValue
UsdSubscriberLocationValue.description: The value of a platform-dependent interface location, represented as an OCTET STRING. A corresponding UsdSubscriberLocationType object will identify the mapping of octets to location elements, e.g. 'slot.port'. Note, when the value of an object having this syntax is encoded as a MIB table INDEX, the rules for encoding a variable-length OCTET STRING are observed.

usdAaaAssignBrasLicense.name: usdAaaAssignBrasLicense
usdAaaAssignBrasLicense.description: The license string that determines the system-wide maximum number of remote user connections allowed. A zero-length string (no license) prohibits remote user connections.

usdAaaAssignBrasLicensedUsers.name: usdAaaAssignBrasLicensedUsers
usdAaaAssignBrasLicensedUsers.description: The system-wide maximum number of remote user connections allowed by the currently configured license string.

usdAaaAssignDomainDelimiters.name: usdAaaAssignDomainDelimiters
usdAaaAssignDomainDelimiters.description: The list of delimiters used to separate the user's name from the user's domain in the username field. The default is '@'.

usdAaaAssignRealmDelimiters.name: usdAaaAssignRealmDelimiters
usdAaaAssignRealmDelimiters.description: The list of delimiters used to separate the user's name from the user's realm in the username field. The realm is treated like the domain in the ERX. The default is none.

usdAaaAssignDomainParseOrder.name: usdAaaAssignDomainParseOrder
usdAaaAssignDomainParseOrder.description: The order in which the user's name is parsed: either search for domain first or realm first in the form (realm/user@domain.com). The default is domain first.

usdAaaAssignSubscriberLimit.name: usdAaaAssignSubscriberLimit
usdAaaAssignSubscriberLimit.description: The maximum number of subscribers permitted in this VR context. The value '0' means no limit.

usdAaaAssignDomainTable.name: usdAaaAssignDomainTable
usdAaaAssignDomainTable.description: The entries in this table specify the assignment of a remote access user to a virtual router, based on the user's domain.

usdAaaAssignDomainEntry.name: usdAaaAssignDomainEntry
usdAaaAssignDomainEntry.description: A specification of the virtual router to which users on a specified domain should be assigned.

usdAaaAssignDomainName.name: usdAaaAssignDomainName
usdAaaAssignDomainName.description: The domain name uniquely identifying this entry.

usdAaaAssignDomainRowStatus.name: usdAaaAssignDomainRowStatus
usdAaaAssignDomainRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table. Only the values 'createAndGo' and 'destroy' may be SET.

usdAaaAssignDomainRouterName.name: usdAaaAssignDomainRouterName
usdAaaAssignDomainRouterName.description: The name of the virtual router to which remote access users within this domain are assigned.

usdAaaAssignDomainLoopback.name: usdAaaAssignDomainLoopback
usdAaaAssignDomainLoopback.description: The number of the loopback interface, associated with the specified virtual router, whose IP address is used as the source address when transmitting IP packets on unnumbered remote access user links. For example, if the associated loopback interface for this domain/router was configured via the console as 'loopback 2', this object would contain the integer value 2. A value of -1 indicates the loopback interface is unspecified.

usdAaaAssignDomainIpHint.name: usdAaaAssignDomainIpHint
usdAaaAssignDomainIpHint.description: Enables/disables the IP hint feature, which causes the system to allocate an IP address before going to RADIUS for authentication.

usdAaaAssignDomainAtmServiceLevel.name: usdAaaAssignDomainAtmServiceLevel
usdAaaAssignDomainAtmServiceLevel.description: The Service category for this circuit: ubr Unspecified bit rate (best effort). ubrPcr Unspecified Bit Rate with Peak Cell Rate limit. nrtVbr Non-realtime Variable Bit Rate. cbr Constant bit rate. Set the service level in combination of the traffic attributes PCR/SCR/MBS in the following matrix for successfull configurations. ServiceLevel PCR SCR MBS ------------------------------------------ ubr omit omit omit ubrPcr must omit omit nrtVbr must must must cbr must omit omit

usdAaaAssignDomainAtmPcr.name: usdAaaAssignDomainAtmPcr
usdAaaAssignDomainAtmPcr.description: Peak Cell Rate, in kilobits per second (kbps), of this circuit. This parameter is only required when usdAaaAssignDomainAtmServiceLevel is configured to have one of the following values: ubrPcr nrtVbr cbr

usdAaaAssignDomainAtmScr.name: usdAaaAssignDomainAtmScr
usdAaaAssignDomainAtmScr.description: Sustained Cell Rate, in kilobits per second (kbps), of this circuit. This parameter is only required when usdAaaAssignDomainAtmServiceLevel is configured to have one of the following values: nrtVbr

usdAaaAssignDomainAtmMbs.name: usdAaaAssignDomainAtmMbs
usdAaaAssignDomainAtmMbs.description: Maximum Burst Size, in cells, of this circuit. This parameter is only required when usdAaaAssugbDomainAtmServiceLevel is configured to have one of the following values: nrtVbr

usdAaaAssignDomainOverrideUserName.name: usdAaaAssignDomainOverrideUserName
usdAaaAssignDomainOverrideUserName.description: The override user name associated with this entry. This object is used to override the username of the remote client.

usdAaaAssignDomainOverridePassword.name: usdAaaAssignDomainOverridePassword
usdAaaAssignDomainOverridePassword.description: The override password for the user name defined by usdAaaAssignDomainOverrideUserName. This object is used to override the password part of the username/password pair of the remote client. This value returns a string length of 0 on reads for security reasons.

usdAaaAssignDomainStripDomain.name: usdAaaAssignDomainStripDomain
usdAaaAssignDomainStripDomain.description: Enables/disables the domain name stripping feature, which causes the system to strip the domain name before sending the access-request to RADIUS for authentication.

usdAaaAssignDomainTunnelTable.name: usdAaaAssignDomainTunnelTable
usdAaaAssignDomainTunnelTable.description: The entries in this table specify the tunnels associated with a domain.

usdAaaAssignDomainTunnelEntry.name: usdAaaAssignDomainTunnelEntry
usdAaaAssignDomainTunnelEntry.description: A specification of the tunnels associated with a domain.

usdAaaAssignDomainTunnelName.name: usdAaaAssignDomainTunnelName
usdAaaAssignDomainTunnelName.description: The domain name associated with this entry.

usdAaaAssignDomainTunnelTag.name: usdAaaAssignDomainTunnelTag
usdAaaAssignDomainTunnelTag.description: The tunnel tag value associated with this entry.

usdAaaAssignDomainTunnelPreference.name: usdAaaAssignDomainTunnelPreference
usdAaaAssignDomainTunnelPreference.description: The tunnel's preference value associated with this entry. The value 0 is the highest preference.

usdAaaAssignDomainTunnelType.name: usdAaaAssignDomainTunnelType
usdAaaAssignDomainTunnelType.description: The tunnel type associated with this entry. Attempts to set this object to tunnelUnknown(2) will fail (wrongValue).

usdAaaAssignDomainTunnelMedium.name: usdAaaAssignDomainTunnelMedium
usdAaaAssignDomainTunnelMedium.description: The tunnel medium associated with this entry. The medium dictates the format of the tunnel address. Attempts to set this object to tunnelMediumUnknown(2) will fail (wrongValue).

usdAaaAssignDomainTunnelAddress.name: usdAaaAssignDomainTunnelAddress
usdAaaAssignDomainTunnelAddress.description: The tunnel server address associated with this entry. The usdAaaAssignDomainTunnelMedium object defines the format of the address. MEDIUM EXAMPLE FORMAT tunnelMedium_IPv4 xyz.xyz.xyz.xyz

usdAaaAssignDomainTunnelPassword.name: usdAaaAssignDomainTunnelPassword
usdAaaAssignDomainTunnelPassword.description: The tunnel password associated with this entry. The object returns a null length string on reads due to security concerns.

usdAaaAssignDomainTunnelId.name: usdAaaAssignDomainTunnelId
usdAaaAssignDomainTunnelId.description: The tunnel identifier associated with this entry. The tunnel identifier is used to distinguish between multiple tunnels to the same usdAaaAssignDomainTunnelAddress.

usdAaaAssignDomainTunnelHostName.name: usdAaaAssignDomainTunnelHostName
usdAaaAssignDomainTunnelHostName.description: The tunnel client hostname associated with this entry. This object is analogous to the RADIUS attribute Tunnel-Client-Auth-ID. When a tunnel is established with a peer, this object can be used to distinguish groups of tunnels.

usdAaaAssignDomainTunnelRowStatus.name: usdAaaAssignDomainTunnelRowStatus
usdAaaAssignDomainTunnelRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table. Only the values 'createAndGo' and 'destroy' may be SET.

usdAaaAssignDomainTunnelServerName.name: usdAaaAssignDomainTunnelServerName
usdAaaAssignDomainTunnelServerName.description: The tunnel server hostname associated with this entry. This object is analogous to the RADIUS attribute Tunnel-Server-Auth-ID. When a tunnel is established with a peer, this object can be used to distinguish groups of tunnels.

usdAaaAssignDomainTunnelClientAddress.name: usdAaaAssignDomainTunnelClientAddress
usdAaaAssignDomainTunnelClientAddress.description: The tunnel client address associated with this entry. The usdAaaAssignDomainTunnelMedium object defines the format of the address. MEDIUM EXAMPLE FORMAT tunnelMedium_IPv4 xyz.xyz.xyz.xyz

usdAaaAuthMethods.name: usdAaaAuthMethods
usdAaaAuthMethods.description: The set of authentication protocols configured on this system. Each octet in this object contains one of the values defined in the UsdAaaAuthenticationMethods TEXTUAL-CONVENTION. The system will sequence through each octet of this object starting at octet 1 and attempt to use the corresponding authentication protocol defined by UsdAaaAuthenticationMethods. Note that if the octet is set to: protocolNone(4) Then authentication does not take place. If an authentication protocol is configured and attempts to reach the authentication server fail, the system will move to the next octet in this object and retry the authentication in the form dictated by the corresponding authentication protocoltype. The process of sequencing thru each octet will stop if the authentication server is successfully contacted, or there are no more configured octets in this object.

usdAaaAcctInterval.name: usdAaaAcctInterval
usdAaaAcctInterval.description: The interval that must elapse between generation of accounting reports, ranging from 10 minutes to 18 hours, or disabled if set to zero.

usdAaaAcctDupServerRouterName.name: usdAaaAcctDupServerRouterName
usdAaaAcctDupServerRouterName.description: The name of another router on this system to which accounting reports should be sent, in addition to or instead of sending accounting reports to the accounting service (if any) configured on the current router (i.e., the router context within which this object instance exists). A zero-length name disables this mechanism.

usdAaaAcctMethods.name: usdAaaAcctMethods
usdAaaAcctMethods.description: The set of accounting protocols configured on this system. Each octet in this object contains one of the values defined in the UsdAaaAccountingMethods TEXTUAL CONVENTION. The system will sequence through each octet of this object starting at octet 1 and attempt to use the corresponding accounting protocol defined by UsdAaaAccountingMethods. Note that if the octet is set to: protocolNone(4) Then accounting is disabled. If an accounting protocol is configured and reports are not successfully generated, the system will move to the next octet in this object and repeat the attempt to generate an accounting report in the form dictated by the corresponding accounting protocol type. The process of sequencing thru each octet will stop if accounting reports are either successfully generated, or there are no more configured octets in this object.

usdAaaAcctSendStopOnAaaDeny.name: usdAaaAcctSendStopOnAaaDeny
usdAaaAcctSendStopOnAaaDeny.description: Enables/disables the accounting stop message sent to the accounting server when authentication server grants access, but AAA denies access.

usdAaaAcctSendStopOnAaaReject.name: usdAaaAcctSendStopOnAaaReject
usdAaaAcctSendStopOnAaaReject.description: Enables/disables the accounting stop message sent to the accounting server when authentication server denies access.

usdAaaAddrPoolDefault.name: usdAaaAddrPoolDefault
usdAaaAddrPoolDefault.description: Identifies the default source of IP address allocation for remote access links: none No address source is specified. Using this setting allows the remote PPP subscriber (client) to set it's own address. local Use the local address pool named 'default'. dhcp Use DHCP service.

usdAaaDupAddrCheck.name: usdAaaDupAddrCheck
usdAaaDupAddrCheck.description: Enables/disables the duplicate IP address checking which causes the system to check the route table for the PPP user's dynamic IP address is provided to PPP (from AAA).

usdAaaAddrDnsPrimary.name: usdAaaAddrDnsPrimary
usdAaaAddrDnsPrimary.description: The IP address of the primary DNS server to be used by remote access clients. A value of 0.0.0.0 indicates no server is configured.

usdAaaAddrDnsSecondary.name: usdAaaAddrDnsSecondary
usdAaaAddrDnsSecondary.description: The IP address of the secondary DNS server to be used by remote access clients. A value of 0.0.0.0 indicates no server is configured.

usdAaaAddrWinsPrimary.name: usdAaaAddrWinsPrimary
usdAaaAddrWinsPrimary.description: The IP address of the primary WINS server to be used by remote access clients. A value of 0.0.0.0 indicates no server is configured.

usdAaaAddrWinsSecondary.name: usdAaaAddrWinsSecondary
usdAaaAddrWinsSecondary.description: The IP address of the secondary WINS server to be used by remote access clients. A value of 0.0.0.0 indicates no server is configured.

usdAaaIdleTimeout.name: usdAaaIdleTimeout
usdAaaIdleTimeout.description: The maximum number of seconds that a user session can be idle before system disconnects the user, ranging from 300 to 7200 seconds, 0 disables idle timeout.

usdAaaSessionTimeout.name: usdAaaSessionTimeout
usdAaaSessionTimeout.description: The maximum number of seconds that a user session can be established before system disconnects the user, ranging from 60 to 604800 seconds, 0 disables session timeout.

usdAaaTunnelClientName.name: usdAaaTunnelClientName
usdAaaTunnelClientName.description: The default tunnel client hostname associated with this virtual router. This object is used when no tunnel client name (client auth ID) is supplied in the authentication response.

usdAaaTunnelPassword.name: usdAaaTunnelPassword
usdAaaTunnelPassword.description: The default tunnel password associated with this virtual router. This object is used when no tunnel password is supplied in the authentication response. The object returns a null length string on reads due to security concerns.

usdAaaTunnelNasPortMethod.name: usdAaaTunnelNasPortMethod
usdAaaTunnelNasPortMethod.description: The default tunnel NAS-port method associated with this virtual router. This object is used to specify the LAC's NAS-port method. This provides limit compatiability to Cisco LNS for the NAS-port method AVP.

usdAaaTunnelIgnoreNasPort.name: usdAaaTunnelIgnoreNasPort
usdAaaTunnelIgnoreNasPort.description: Enables/disables the use of the NAS-port value that is passed in from the tunnel application.

usdAaaTunnelIgnoreNasPortType.name: usdAaaTunnelIgnoreNasPortType
usdAaaTunnelIgnoreNasPortType.description: Enables/disables the use of the NAS-port-type value that is passed in from the tunnel application.

usdAaaTunnelAssignmentIdFormat.name: usdAaaTunnelAssignmentIdFormat
usdAaaTunnelAssignmentIdFormat.description: The tunnel assignment ID format for distinguishing tunnel definitions. This object is used to specify the tunnel assigment ID format passed to the LAC. The value assignmentId(0) indicates that the original tunnel assignment ID value is to be used; clientServerId(1) indicates that the concatenated value from client-auth-name, server-auth-name, and assignment-id is to be used.

usdAaaIncomingInitiateRequests.name: usdAaaIncomingInitiateRequests
usdAaaIncomingInitiateRequests.description: The number of AAA incoming initiate requests

usdAaaIncomingTerminateRequests.name: usdAaaIncomingTerminateRequests
usdAaaIncomingTerminateRequests.description: The number of AAA incomining termination requests

usdAaaOutgoingTunnelGrantResponses.name: usdAaaOutgoingTunnelGrantResponses
usdAaaOutgoingTunnelGrantResponses.description: The number of AAA outgoing tunnel grant responses

usdAaaOutgoingGrantResponses.name: usdAaaOutgoingGrantResponses
usdAaaOutgoingGrantResponses.description: The number of AAA outgoing grant responses

usdAaaOutgoingDenyResponses.name: usdAaaOutgoingDenyResponses
usdAaaOutgoingDenyResponses.description: The number of AAA outgoing deny responses

usdAaaOutgoingErrorResponses.name: usdAaaOutgoingErrorResponses
usdAaaOutgoingErrorResponses.description: The number of AAA outgoing error responses

usdAaaOutgoingAuthRequests.name: usdAaaOutgoingAuthRequests
usdAaaOutgoingAuthRequests.description: The number of AAA outgoing authentication requests

usdAaaIncomingAuthResponses.name: usdAaaIncomingAuthResponses
usdAaaIncomingAuthResponses.description: The number of AAA incoming authentication responses

usdAaaOutgoingReAuthRequests.name: usdAaaOutgoingReAuthRequests
usdAaaOutgoingReAuthRequests.description: The number of AAA outgoing re-authentication requests

usdAaaIncomingReAuthResponses.name: usdAaaIncomingReAuthResponses
usdAaaIncomingReAuthResponses.description: The number of AAA incoming re-authentication responses

usdAaaOutgoingAcctRequests.name: usdAaaOutgoingAcctRequests
usdAaaOutgoingAcctRequests.description: The number of AAA outgoing accounting requests

usdAaaIncomingAcctResponses.name: usdAaaIncomingAcctResponses
usdAaaIncomingAcctResponses.description: The number of AAA incoming accounting responses

usdAaaOutgoingDupAcctRequests.name: usdAaaOutgoingDupAcctRequests
usdAaaOutgoingDupAcctRequests.description: The number of AAA outgoing duplicate accounting requests

usdAaaIncomingDupAcctResponses.name: usdAaaIncomingDupAcctResponses
usdAaaIncomingDupAcctResponses.description: The number of AAA incoing duplication accounting responses

usdAaaOutgoingAddrRequests.name: usdAaaOutgoingAddrRequests
usdAaaOutgoingAddrRequests.description: The number of AAA outgoing address requests

usdAaaIncomingAddrResponses.name: usdAaaIncomingAddrResponses
usdAaaIncomingAddrResponses.description: The number of AAA incoming address responses

usdAaaSubscriberMaxCount.name: usdAaaSubscriberMaxCount
usdAaaSubscriberMaxCount.description: The configuration setting for the maximum number of subscribers. There is a grace number of subscribers above this limit, which when reached will cause authentication requests to be denied.

usdAaaSubscriberPeakCount.name: usdAaaSubscriberPeakCount
usdAaaSubscriberPeakCount.description: The peak number of subscribers. The peak count includes successfully authenticated subscribers as well as those subscribers in the process of being authenticated.

usdAaaSubscriberCount.name: usdAaaSubscriberCount
usdAaaSubscriberCount.description: The current number of subscribers. The subscriber count includes successfully authenticated subscribers as well as those subscribers in the process of being authenticated.

usdAaaSubscriberTable.name: usdAaaSubscriberTable
usdAaaSubscriberTable.description: The entries in this table represent subscribers by subscriber handle value.

usdAaaSubscriberEntry.name: usdAaaSubscriberEntry
usdAaaSubscriberEntry.description: A specification of subscribers by subscriber handle.

usdAaaSubscriberHandle.name: usdAaaSubscriberHandle
usdAaaSubscriberHandle.description: The subscriber handle associated with this subscriber. A subscriber handle is a monotomically increasing integer.

usdAaaSubscriberUserName.name: usdAaaSubscriberUserName
usdAaaSubscriberUserName.description: The RADIUS userName associated with this subscriber.

usdAaaSubscriberRouterName.name: usdAaaSubscriberRouterName
usdAaaSubscriberRouterName.description: The virtual router assigned to this subscriber.

usdAaaSubscriberRouterIndex.name: usdAaaSubscriberRouterIndex
usdAaaSubscriberRouterIndex.description: The router index that identifies the virtual router associated with this subscriber. The value of this object can be used to index the router in the usdRouterTable.

usdAaaSubscriberLoginTime.name: usdAaaSubscriberLoginTime
usdAaaSubscriberLoginTime.description: The time this subscriber logged in to RADIUS server.

usdAaaSubscriberIpAddress.name: usdAaaSubscriberIpAddress
usdAaaSubscriberIpAddress.description: The client IP Address assigned to this subscriber.

usdAaaSubscriberIpAddressMask.name: usdAaaSubscriberIpAddressMask
usdAaaSubscriberIpAddressMask.description: The client IP Address Mask assigned to this subscriber.

usdAaaSubscriberAddrAssignType.name: usdAaaSubscriberAddrAssignType
usdAaaSubscriberAddrAssignType.description: The address assignment type for this subscriber.

usdAaaSubscriberInterfaceId.name: usdAaaSubscriberInterfaceId
usdAaaSubscriberInterfaceId.description: A text string describing the local interface associated with this subscriber. Types/formats/examples for this string include: ATM Virtual Circuit atm <slot>/<port>:<vpi>.<vci> 'atm 3/0:0.100' Ethernet { fastEthernet | gigabitEthernet } <slot>/<port> 'fastEthernet 3/0' 'gigabitEthernet 3/0' Ethernet VLAN { fastEthernet | gigabitEthernet } <slot>/<port>:<vlanID> 'fastEthernet 3/0:1000' 'gigabitEthernet 3/0:1000' Channelized Serial serial <slot>/<port>:<channelSpecifier>[/<channelSpecifier>]* 'serial 3/0:4' (T1/E1) 'serial 3/0:2/4' (T3/E3) 'serial 3/0:2/1/1/4' (OC3/OC12 - channelized DS3) 'serial 3/0:2/1/1/1/4' (OC3/OC12 - virtual tributaries) L2TP/L2F over IP ip:<localIpAddr>:<peerIpAddr>:<localTunnelID>:<peerTunnelID>: <localSessionID>:<peerSessionID>:<callSerialNumber> 'ip:10.10.0.1:20.20.0.2:1234:5678:9abc:def0:6789abcd' (Note: tunnelIDs, sessionIDs, and callSerialNumber are in hexadecimal.) Other formats may be supported over time.

usdAaaSubscriberClientType.name: usdAaaSubscriberClientType
usdAaaSubscriberClientType.description: The client type for this subscriber. Certain client types (e.g., 'other') might be suppressed from representation in this table.

usdAaaSubscriberIngressPolicyName.name: usdAaaSubscriberIngressPolicyName
usdAaaSubscriberIngressPolicyName.description: The Ingress Policy Name associated with this subscriber.

usdAaaSubscriberEgressPolicyName.name: usdAaaSubscriberEgressPolicyName
usdAaaSubscriberEgressPolicyName.description: The Egress Policy Name associated with this subscriber.

usdAaaSubscriberQosProfileName.name: usdAaaSubscriberQosProfileName
usdAaaSubscriberQosProfileName.description: The QoS Profile Name associated with this subscriber.

usdAaaSubscriberRowStatus.name: usdAaaSubscriberRowStatus
usdAaaSubscriberRowStatus.description: Controls the deletion of the subscriber from this table. Deletion of the subscriber is analogous to logging the subscriber out of the network. Note: only 'destroy' is supported for SNMP SET operations.

usdAaaSubscriberRouterSummaryTable.name: usdAaaSubscriberRouterSummaryTable
usdAaaSubscriberRouterSummaryTable.description: The entries in this table report number of subscribers per router.

usdAaaSubscriberRouterSummaryEntry.name: usdAaaSubscriberRouterSummaryEntry
usdAaaSubscriberRouterSummaryEntry.description: A specification of subscribers for a router.

usdAaaSubscriberRouterSummaryRouterIndex.name: usdAaaSubscriberRouterSummaryRouterIndex
usdAaaSubscriberRouterSummaryRouterIndex.description: The router index of the virtual router. The value of this object can be used to retrieve additional information in the router mib.

usdAaaSubscriberRouterSummaryCount.name: usdAaaSubscriberRouterSummaryCount
usdAaaSubscriberRouterSummaryCount.description: The number of subscribers on this router.

usdAaaSubscriberRouterTable.name: usdAaaSubscriberRouterTable
usdAaaSubscriberRouterTable.description: The entries in this table sort subscribers by router ID.

usdAaaSubscriberRouterEntry.name: usdAaaSubscriberRouterEntry
usdAaaSubscriberRouterEntry.description: A specification of subscribers by router ID.

usdAaaSubscriberRouterRouterIndex.name: usdAaaSubscriberRouterRouterIndex
usdAaaSubscriberRouterRouterIndex.description: The router index of the virtual router. The value of this object can be used to retrieve additional information in the router MIB.

usdAaaSubscriberRouterHandle.name: usdAaaSubscriberRouterHandle
usdAaaSubscriberRouterHandle.description: The subscriber handle associated with this subscriber. A subscriber handle is a monotonically increasing integer.

usdAaaSubscriberLocationType.name: usdAaaSubscriberLocationType
usdAaaSubscriberLocationType.description: Describes the interpretation of UsdSubscriberLocationValue object values into platform-dependent interface location components, e.g., 'slot.port'.

usdAaaSubscriberLocationSummaryTable.name: usdAaaSubscriberLocationSummaryTable
usdAaaSubscriberLocationSummaryTable.description: The entries in this table report number of subscribers per interface location.

usdAaaSubscriberLocationSummaryEntry.name: usdAaaSubscriberLocationSummaryEntry
usdAaaSubscriberLocationSummaryEntry.description: A specification of subscribers on an interface location.

usdAaaSubscriberLocationSummaryLocationI.name: usdAaaSubscriberLocationSummaryLocationIndex
usdAaaSubscriberLocationSummaryLocationI.description: The value of a platform interface location.

usdAaaSubscriberLocationSummaryCount.name: usdAaaSubscriberLocationSummaryCount
usdAaaSubscriberLocationSummaryCount.description: The number of subscribers associated with this interface location.

usdAaaSubscriberLocationTable.name: usdAaaSubscriberLocationTable
usdAaaSubscriberLocationTable.description: The entries in this table sort subscribers by interface location.

usdAaaSubscriberLocationEntry.name: usdAaaSubscriberLocationEntry
usdAaaSubscriberLocationEntry.description: An association of a subscriber to an interface location.

usdAaaSubscriberLocationLocationIndex.name: usdAaaSubscriberLocationLocationIndex
usdAaaSubscriberLocationLocationIndex.description: The value of a platform interface location.

usdAaaSubscriberLocationHandle.name: usdAaaSubscriberLocationHandle

usdAaaSubscriberPseudoPeakCount.name: usdAaaSubscriberPseudoPeakCount
usdAaaSubscriberPseudoPeakCount.description: The peak number of pseudo-subscribers. The peak count includes successfully authenticated pseudo-subscribers as well as those pseudo-subscribers in the process of being authenticated. Pseudo-subscribers are those whose identities are locally configured on a dynamic link (e.g. an ATM subinterface) via the (imprecisely named) Unisphere-Data-SUBSCRIBER-MIB. Some links (e.g. IPoA) provide no link protocol with which to query the identity of a remote user. In such a case, a locally configured pseudo-subscriber can be used to conduct AAA authentication-based configuration of the dynamic link when it becomes active. Pseudo-subscribers are understood to be intended more for dynamic configuration than for actually identifying the remote user. Consequently, the pseudo-subscribers are not reflected in any of the subscriber tables defined in this MIB.
